messages.message: i know `aihub-derived-field` is a non-blocking test, but fyi it failed in my CI run (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/13892/overview/19bb831c-bb8c-49c9-9df2-e81b663973a8?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1) @danny.lan

interesting, it failed 1/4 runs in the `afterAll` logic so it looks flaky, the `PUT extracted_fields` call failed after deleting a field with `Field missing. '84739'`.

Even though we fail to save `extracted_fields` it doesn’t necessarily seem to be a “bug” since no error is shown to the user and we can still use the old `extracted_fields` which just has some extra data in it now.
hmm should we intercept the `PUT extracted_fields` call or do something else so that Cypress doesn’t think that this counts as a test failure?
